Two-time Grammy award-winning singer, songwriter and sometime actor, Gregory Porter has returned to South Africa. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more details. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Two-time Grammy award-winning singer, and songwriter, Gregory Porter has returned to South Africa. READ: Jon Batiste: the jazz master set to serenade Macron Porter will be performing at the Kirstenbosch National Botanical Garden on Saturday. His fourth album, Take Me to the Alley, earned him his second Grammy for Best Jazz Vocal Album in 2017. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more details in the video.